headline: Prudential Names Morgan Stanley’s Chappuis to Succeed Hunt as PGIM CEO
summary: The insurance company tabbed Morgan Stanley veteran Jacques Chappuis to succeed David Hunt at the helm of the Prudential’s $1.4 trillion investment-management business.

headline: MSIM Adds Latest Strategy, Parametric Equity Plus, to $3.3 Billion ETF Platform
summary: NEW YORK, November 08, 2024--Morgan Stanley Investment Management ("MSIM") today announced the launch of its latest ETF, Parametric Equity Plus ETF (Ticker: "PEPS"), a US large-cap equity strategy. Since the introduction of MSIM’s first ETFs in 2023, the platform has grown to over $3.3 billion in ETF assets with 16 total strategies that span asset classes and themes. headline: Morgan Stanley’s Legal Woes Mount With Judge’s Latest Deferred-Comp Decision
